comment_regular_data.body:
Added another builtin fallback win-term terminfo which is mainly for WT.
I modified the terminfo.c with the following : 
```c++
} else if (terminfo_is_term_family(term, "vtpcon") && getenv("WT_SESSION")) {
  *termname = xstrdup("builtin_win_term");
  return unibi_from_mem((const char *)windows_terminal_terminfo,
                        sizeof windows_terminal_terminfo);
```
which specificly targeting WT. with this no more conflict is there with unsupported terminals for example the legacy command line .

![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/27051374/901210fb-2731-4009-8a4f-b301aa3e3735)

Left: with the mentioned addition of a win-term terminfo fallback
Right: without (the vtpcon only modified terminfo)

notice that stylized underlines are not supported in the command prompt terminal .

Another approach is to add a condition here instead of adding a terminfo entry:
```c
  // Extended underline.
  // terminfo will have Smulx for this (but no support for colors yet).
  tui->unibi_ext.set_underline_style = unibi_find_ext_str(ut, "Smulx");
  if (tui->unibi_ext.set_underline_style == -1) {
    int ext_bool_Su = unibi_find_ext_bool(ut, "Su");  // used by kitty
    if (vte_version >= 5102 || konsolev >= 221170
        || (ext_bool_Su != -1
            && unibi_get_ext_bool(ut, (size_t)ext_bool_Su))) {
      tui->unibi_ext.set_underline_style = (int)unibi_add_ext_str(ut, "ext.set_underline_style",
                                                                  "\x1b[4:%p1%dm");
    }
  }
```
Since there are already several conditions, I'm not sure which solution is better.

